Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for React + Vite Portfolio Project
=====================================================================

Summary:
--------
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights following the official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

Changes Made:
-------------

1. Package Installation:
   - Installed @vercel/speed-insights v2.0.0 as a dependency
   - Updated package.json with the new dependency
   - Updated package-lock.json with the complete dependency tree

2. Code Changes:
   - Modified: src/App.jsx
     * Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react'`
     * Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the App component's JSX return statement
     * Placed at the top of the component tree for optimal tracking

Implementation Details:
-----------------------
- Framework: React + Vite (identified from package.json and vite.config.js)
- Installation method: npm (using package-lock.json)
- Integration point: Main App component (src/App.jsx)
- Followed official Vercel documentation for React framework integration

Testing & Verification:
-----------------------
✅ Build completed successfully (vite build)
✅ No new linting errors introduced by the changes
✅ Package dependencies properly installed and locked

Next Steps:
-----------
After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard
2. Select your project and click the Enable button
3. Deploy the application to activate tracking
4. Verify the tracking script appears in the page's head tag
5. Monitor performance metrics in the Speed Insights dashboard

Notes:
------
- The SpeedInsights component is lightweight and has no visual impact
- It automatically tracks Web Vitals and performance metrics once deployed on Vercel
- The component is placed at the top level of the App component for comprehensive page tracking
- All existing functionality and code structure has been preserved
